---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro"
---

<Layout title = "About">
    <div class="container">
        <h1 class="title has-text-centered is-1 py-4 has-text-primary">About Atmos</h1>
        <div class="columns m-6">
            <div class="column is-4">
                <div class="box">
                    <h3 class="title mb-3">Who are we?</h3>
                    <p>Atmos is a cutting-edge weather forecasting platform founded in 2023 by a team of meteorologists and software engineers. We combine advanced AI algorithms with real-time satellite data to provide the most accurate weather predictions available. Our mission is to make weather information accessible, reliable, and beautifully presented for everyone from casual users to professional forecasters.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="column is-4">
                <div class="box">
                    <h3 class="title mb-3">What is our goal?</h3>
                    <p>Our goal is to revolutionize how people interact with weather data. We believe weather forecasting should be intuitive, accurate, and visually engaging. By leveraging machine learning and hyperlocal data sources, we aim to provide 5-day forecasts with 95% accuracy. We're committed to helping communities prepare for weather events and make informed decisions about their daily activities.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="column is-4">
                <div class="box">
                    <h3 class="title mb-3">What does Atmos cost?</h3>
                    <p><strong>Completely free!</strong></p>
                    <p>Atmos is funded through partnerships with meteorological institutes and research grants. We believe accurate weather information is a public service that should be accessible to everyone, regardless of economic status. No ads, no subscriptions, no hidden fees - just reliable weather data when you need it most.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="mx-6" />

        <h2 class="title has-text-centered is-2 py-4 has-text-primary">Our Technology</h2>
        <div class="columns m-6">
            <div class="column is-6">
                <div class="box">
                    <h3 class="title mb-3">Advanced AI Forecasting</h3>
                    <p>Our proprietary neural networks analyze over 50 million data points daily from satellites, weather stations, and atmospheric sensors. Using deep learning algorithms trained on 30 years of historical weather patterns, we can predict weather changes up to 7 days in advance with unprecedented accuracy.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="column is-6">
                <div class="box">
                    <h3 class="title mb-3">Real-time Data Integration</h3>
                    <p>Atmos connects to over 10,000 weather stations worldwide, processing live atmospheric data every 15 minutes. Our system automatically adjusts forecasts based on changing conditions, ensuring you always have the most current weather information available.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="mx-6" />

        <h2 class="title has-text-centered is-2 py-4 has-text-primary">Meet Our Team</h2>
        <div class="columns m-6">
            <div class="column is-4">
                <div class="box has-text-centered">
                    <h4 class="title is-4 mb-3">Dr. Sarah Chen</h4>
                    <p class="subtitle is-6 mb-3">Chief Meteorologist</p>
                    <p>PhD in Atmospheric Sciences from MIT. Former NASA researcher with 15 years of experience in climate modeling and weather prediction systems.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="column is-4">
                <div class="box has-text-centered">
                    <h4 class="title is-4 mb-3">Marcus Andersson</h4>
                    <p class="subtitle is-6 mb-3">Lead Developer</p>
                    <p>Full-stack engineer specializing in real-time data processing. Previously worked at Google developing large-scale weather visualization systems.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="column is-4">
                <div class="box has-text-centered">
                    <h4 class="title is-4 mb-3">Dr. Elena Rodriguez</h4>
                    <p class="subtitle is-6 mb-3">AI Research Director</p>
                    <p>Machine learning expert with PhD from Stanford. Pioneered the deep learning algorithms that power Atmos's forecasting accuracy.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>